In [4]:
mbids_dataset=[]  # the list of 4 sets of mbids

for ds in datasets:
    mbids=[]
    
    with open(ds[1]) as f:
        reader = csv.reader(f, delimiter='\t')
        next(reader)
        for line in reader:
            mbids.append(line[0])
    f.close()
    
    mbids_dataset.append(set(mbids))

for i, v in enumerate(mbids_dataset):

In [6]:
from copy import deepcopy
mbids_intersection_set = deepcopy(mbids_dataset[0])
for s in mbids_dataset[1:]:
    # mbids_intersection_set : the set containing all the mbids occuring in all four datasets
    mbids_intersection_set = mbids_intersection_set.intersection(s)

In [8]:
# my_dataset = the dictionary containing key = mbid and value = list of subgenres
my_dataset= {key:[] for key in mbids_intersection_set}
In [9]:
genres=set()  # Set containing all the genres occuring atleast once stored in the format source---genre---subgenre
genres_dict={} # Dictionary with genre names as key and number of occurences as value
for ds in datasets:
    with open(ds[1]) as f:
        reader = csv.reader(f, delimiter='\t')
        for line in reader:
            if line[0] in mbids_intersection_set:      # line[0] == mbid for each item in mbids_intersection_set
                for x in line:
                    # making use of the fact that all subgenres are listed in the genre---subgenre format in the db
                    if '---' in x:                      
                        this_genre = ds[0]+'---'+x
                        my_dataset[line[0]].append(this_genre)  # add the genre to the mbid: [subgenres] dataset 
                        genres.add(this_genre)  # add the genre to the set of all genres
                        # if the genre is not existing initialize to 0 and add one on every occurence                        
                        genres_dict[this_genre]= genres_dict.get(this_genre, 0) + 1 
                        
print(len(genres))  # How many different subgenres are present

1605
In [10]:
for (key , value) in genres_dict.items():  # select the subgenres that occur atleast 500 times
    if value < 500:
        genres.remove(key)

In [13]:
matrix = np.empty([len(row_names), len(col_names)])   # the mbid-subgenre occurence matrix
with open('my_dataset.csv', 'w') as wf:
    writer = csv.writer(wf, delimiter='\t')
    
    # Write the header for csv file
    header = np.hstack(('recordingmbid', col_names))
    writer.writerow(header)
   
    # read my_dataset dictionary line by line to write the csv file as well as to populate the occurence matrix
    # in a single pass
    for key, value in my_dataset.items():
        i = np.where(row_names==key)[0]
        for v in value:
            if (v!=[]):
                j = np.where(col_names == v)[0]
                matrix[i,j] = 1 
        data = np.hstack((key, value))
        writer.writerow(data)
